      "date": "2026-03-16T17:29:59.000Z",
      "content": "The model `gpt-5.4` behaves strangely regarding `F1 Score`.\nOn the setting \"Default Reasoning / Default Temperature\", it is a strong outlier in terms of not degrading the `F1 Score` too much on the *Hard* dataset (4%) vs. *Normal* dataset (98%) (bottom right point in the scatterplot).\n\n[image.png](/user_uploads/5/50/p14FI-kr3aW1FCdwz2d8y4y8/image.png)\n\nAdditionally, on the *Hard* dataset, this model performs better on \"Low Reasoning / Low Temperature\" setting (F1=16.9%) than on \"Default Reasoning / Default Temperature\" setting (F1=4%).\n\nI believe that `gpt-5.4` is getting more tokens for reasoning on Low compared to Default setting :sweat_smile:",
